<doc id="1093596" wikidata="Q7804530" url="?curid=1093596" title="Tim Wynveen">
<text>Tim Wynveen is a Canadian novelist. His 1997 debut novel, &quot;Angel Falls&quot;, won the Commonwealth Writers Prize for Best First Book. He subsequently published &quot;Balloon&quot; in 1999 and &quot;Sweeter Life&quot; in 2003.

Raised in Leamington, Ontario, he moved to Toronto in the 1970s to play music, his first passion. He was the guitar player for a while with Edward Bear and later Chris De Burgh from Ireland.

